===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{context|conjunctive}} [[nevertheless|Nevertheless]], [[nonetheless]], [[even so]], [[that said]], [[in spite of]] this.
#: ''He told me not to do it; '''however''', I did it.''
# {{context|degree}} To whatever degree.
#: '''''However''' clear you think you've been, many questions will remain.''
# {{chiefly|British|as an intensified form in interrogatives}} In what way; [[how]].
#: '''''However''' did you do that?''

====Usage notes====
{{unreferenced}}
* {{sense|nevertheless}} Strunk and White’s ''[[w:The Elements of Style|The Elements of Style]]'' argues that the adverb ''however'', in its sense of {{term|nevertheless|lang=en}} should be avoided at the beginning of a sentence. Other style guides<!-- Which ones? --> argue that ''however'' is overused in this sense, whether or not at the start of a sentence.

